<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATHAN W. SHOCK; GERONTOLOGIST PIONEERED AGING RESEARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nathan W. Shock, 82, a gerontologist who was among the first to explore the 
physiology of aging on the various organs. As director of the pioneering 
federal Gerontology Research Center in Baltimore, Dr. Shock and his colleagues 
did years of research that proved that parts of the body age at different 
rates, as do individuals. He had moved to Baltimore from Berkeley in 1941 to 
join the first research program on aging for the National Institutes of Health. 
He also was scientific director of the National Institute on Aging for a year 
before retiring in 1976. In Baltimore on Sunday of cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
