<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAGIC'S EJECTION LEFT FAN DEJECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Imagine my excitement going to the Lakers' opener and getting to see an 
injury-free Magic Johnson back in action. Imagine my rage 3 1/2 minutes into 
the game when the official threw the league's MVP (and the Suns' Kevin Johnson) 
out of the game for a harmless shoving match. I appreciate the officials trying 
to keep the game clean, but when they deny 17,000 high-paying customers the 
right to see their hero because of a silly scrape, the NBA has committed the 
ultimate technical foul. 
</P>
<P>
If the league expects fans to pay to see their game, they better provide the 
product. 
</P>
<P>
And shame on referees Bill Oakes, Greg Willard and David Jones. The 
double-ejection was a gutsy call. And totally brainless. 
</P>
<P>
RICK WALLACE, Malibu 
</P>
