<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOVIETS DEFEAT U.S. IN VOLLEYBALL OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Soviet Union men's volleyball team defeated the United States, 16-14, 5-15, 
15-11, 4-15, 15-13 in the opening round of the eight-team World Cup at Osaka, 
Japan. 
</P>
<P>
The United States meets Cuba next in the round-robin tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Other opening round scores: Cuba defeated Brazil, 16-14, 15-5, 15-9; Italy beat 
Cameroon, 15-2, 15-1, 15-4, and South Korea defeated Japan, 11-15, 7-15, 15-12, 
16-14, 17-15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
