<HEADLINE>
<P>
WRETHAM NARROW WINNER IN HOLLYWOOD PARK FEATURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Favored Wretham beat 6-1 shot J.T.'s Pet by a head in the $45,000 allowance 
feature Friday for his second U.S. victory, both on the turf at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
Less than a half-length separated the first four finishers as Master Treaty was 
a neck back in third and Silver Circus a head back in fourth. 
</P>
<P>
Wretham, ridden by Laffit Pincay, covered the 1 1-16 miles in 1:41 and paid $7, 
$4.20 and $4.20 as the favorite of the crowd of 16,270. 
</P>
<P>
The 4-year-old gelding from England, trained by Neil Drysdale, won $24,750 for 
Relatively Stable, pushing his 1989 earnings to $57,600. 
</P>
<P>
J.T.'s Pet, ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye at 116 pounds, one less than the 
winner, paid $6.20 and $4.20. Master Treaty, with Alex Solis and 115 pounds, 
paid $7.20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
