<HEADLINE>
<P>
CROSS-COUNTRY, VOLLEYBALL FINALS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
High school cross-country championships for both boys and girls, and girls' 
volleyball finals are scheduled today in the Southern Section and City. 
</P>
<P>
At Mt. San Antonio College, beginning at 7:30 a.m., the Southern Section 
cross-country finals will feature Palos Verdes in the girls' 4-A Division going 
for its fifth consecutive title and Maranatha shooting for its fourth 
consecutive title in the 1-A Division. 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo is a solid favorite to win the 4-A boys title, but close contests can 
be expected in the 3-A between Newhall Hart and San Gabriel; in the 2-A between 
Arroyo Grande and Agoura; and in the 1-A between Whittier Christian and Long 
Beach St. Anthony. 
</P>
<P>
The City cross-country finals are scheduled at Pierce College at 10 a.m. Taft, 
Belmont and Venice are the teams to watch in the boys' race. In the girls' 
race, Taft, Belmont, Birmingham and San Pedro are the title contenders. 
</P>
<P>
In girls' volleyball, Mira Costa of Manhattan Beach (22-0) and Corona del Mar 
of Newport Beach (22-1), widely regarded as the Nos. 1 and 2 teams in the 
nation, will meet tonight at 8:15 in the Southern Section 5-A final at Marina 
High in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Also at Marina High, Simi Valley Royal (18-1) will play Anaheim Esperanza 
(17-1) for the 4-A title at 6:15; La Habra (17-1) meets Agoura (15-3) for the 
3-A championship at 3:30; top-seeded Palos Verdes Chadwick (18-0) plays 
Pasadena Mayfield (14-6), a wild-card entry, for the Small Schools championship 
at 1:30; and St. Anthony (20-0) plays Brentwood (17-0) in the 1-A final at 
11:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
At the Wooden Center on the UCLA campus, Palisades plays Chatsworth for the 
City 4-A title at 8 p.m., and Garfield meets Birmingham for the 3-A title at 
5:30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
