<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSULT TO SOVIET VISITORS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re Donna Perlmutter's critique of the Red Army Chorus: I am convinced that with 
the ingrained attitudes and low level of public awareness in the "Free" World, 
the Cold War will never end ("The Red Army Chorus -- A Show of Strength, 
Inside, Outside Shrine," Nov. 4). It was a display of mass rudeness for the 
Armenians -- "1,000 protesting emigres" -- to insult the members of the Red 
Army Chorus, guests of the United States. It is a sad commentary on the brave 
new world when art has to be used as a political weapon. 
</P>
<P>
JAMES REESE 
</P>
<P>
Banning 
</P>
</TEXT>
