<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIVERS SCORES 24 POINTS TO LEAD SAN GORGONIO PAST OCEAN VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAM CEREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Running back Ron Rivers rushed for 170 yards and scored 24 points to lead San 
Bernardino's San Gorgonio High School over Ocean View, 32-24, at Huntington 
Beach High Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
"It all came easily after the line started blocking," Rivers said. 
</P>
<P>
Rivers scored three touchdowns, one in each of the first three quarters, 
including a 37-yard return of an interception. He also scored three two-point 
conversions. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View scored on a 16-yard pass from Randy Karliner to Albert Fanaga three 
minutes into the game, but the Seahawks didn't score another touchdown until 
they scored twice in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
"We had the opportunities," Ocean View Coach Howard Isom said, "but we just 
didn't capitalize on them." 
</P>
<P>
Karliner completed seven of 15 passes for 129 yards, but San Gorgonio sacked 
him seven times. 
</P>
<P>
"They're a good team," San Gorgonio Coach Karl Gayton said. "This is the first 
time we weren't able to just run up the middle." PAM CEREN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111889-0053 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 136521 </DOCID>
