<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
IN ANOTHER NORTH VALLEY LEAGUE GAME: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TODD JACOBSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Granada Hills 20, Chatsworth 6 -- Quarterback Bryan Martin completed 15 of 35 
for 178 yards and three touchdowns to lead Granada Hills (10-0, 7-0) over 
Chatsworth (3-5-1, 2-5), which was eliminated from playoff consideration. 
</P>
<P>
Martin threw scoring passes of 10, four and four yards. Brett Washington led 
Granada Hills with 49 yards in 15 carries. Washington caught a 10-yard 
touchdown pass in the first quarter and a four-yard touchdown pass in the 
fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth scored its only touchdown when linebacker Scott Lawrence forced a 
Martin fumble, and Montay Hardison returned it 43 yards for the score. 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills limited Chatsworth to eight yards passing and 86 yards rushing. 
The Granada Hills offense rolled up 236 yards but had only 58 on the ground. 
TODD JACOBSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
