<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WEST VALLEY LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cleveland 31, Canoga Park 7 -- Reserve quarterback Aaronn Castro, a freshman, 
ran for touchdowns of 10 and seven yards as the Cavaliers (4-5, 3-4) secured a 
berth in the 4-A playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Castro entered the game in the second quarter and shared time with Steve 
Bryant, who completed eight of 11 passes for 111 yards. Castro completed four 
of four passes for 45 yards and scored on his only two carries. 
</P>
<P>
Tailback Pat Bryant led Cleveland rushers with 77 yards in 14 carries, his last 
a 46-yard touchdown to complete the scoring. 
</P>
<P>
Canoga Park tailback Scott Byrd rushed for 64 yards in 16 carries and scored 
the Hunters' only touchdown on a six-yard run. Quarterback David Erhardt 
completed 10 of 25 passes for 81 yards with one interception for the Hunters 
(1-8, 1-6). GREG MEADE 
</P>
