<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Barbara 44, Crescenta Valley 7 -- Defensive end Colby Bogust picked a 
Santa Barbara fumble out of the air and returned it 57 yards in the first 
quarter for a Crescenta Valley touchdown and the Falcons' only bright spot. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara (10-1) proceeded to score 44 unanswered points. 
</P>
<P>
Pancho Renteria completed 10 of 14 passes for 153 yards and two touchdowns. He 
also rushed for 22 yards and another score. Crescenta Valley (6-5) was limited 
to minus-4 yards in total offense in the first half and turned the ball over 
five times in the game. GREG GUSS 
