<P>
DIVISION VII 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE BARNATHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chaminade 10, Verbum Dei 6 -- Defensive back Dan Kelly tackled Verbum Dei 
running back Artis Houston at the Chaminade three-yard line as time ran out to 
give Chaminade the victory at home. 
</P>
<P>
Verbum Dei (6-5) drove 76 yards in 10 plays from its own 18-yard line in the 
final minutes before Kelly made the game-saving tackle on a first-and-goal play 
from the six. 
</P>
<P>
With Chaminade (8-2) trailing in the first quarter, 6-0, Felix Goodson returned 
a kickoff 88 yards. Mike Terzian added a 36-yard field goal with 8:15 to play 
to put Chaminade ahead, 10-6. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade's Colin Havert rushed for 143 yards in 23 carries. Next week, the 
Eagles play Lompoc, a 38-23 winner over Mira Costa. LEE BARNATHAN 
</P>
