<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CEBALLOS PACES TITANS TO EXHIBITION VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cedric Ceballos scored 29 points and 13 rebounds to lead Cal State Fullerton to 
a 97-91 victory over East Melbourne of Australia in an exhibition basketball 
game Friday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Ceballos, a senior forward, was 13 of 21 from the field. Mark Hills added 27 
and Wayne Williams had 25 for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
In the National Intercollegiate clay court championships at the Rod Laver 
Tennis Center in Hilton Head, S.C., UC Irvine's Trevor Kronemann was upset in 
the second round. 
</P>
<P>
Kronemann, the No. 2 seeded player in the tournament and fourth-ranked 
collegiate player in the nation, was defeated by Mark Jeffrey of Mississippi 
State, 7-6 (7-5), 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 3, Cal State Dominguez Hills 0 -- Rena Strange had nine kills to lead 
Chapman to a 15-13, 15-3, 15-1 victory. Dana Beardsley added six kills for 
Chapman (25-5, 9-3). 
</P>
</TEXT>
