<P>
MEDIATOR SETS NEW TALKS IN LONG BOEING STRIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A federal mediator said Friday that he has called the Boeing Co. and the union 
representing 57,800 striking machinists back to the bargaining table in another 
attempt to end the longest walkout ever against the world's largest airplane 
manufacturer. 
</P>
<P>
Mediator Doug Hammond said he scheduled a session beginning this afternoon. The 
strike by members of the International Assn. of Machinists and Aerospace 
Workers entered its 45th day Friday, tying the record set by the last strike 
against Boeing in 1977. 
</P>
