<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six men accused of operating a large-scale crack cocaine ring in Gainesville, 
Fla., which had made past sales to University of Florida athletes, were found 
guilty of conspiracy charges. 
</P>
<P>
The jury deliberated five hours before finding the six guilty of conspiracy to 
distribute cocaine. 
</P>
<P>
According to testimony, at least two of the defendants -- Eric Eugene Scott and 
Kelvin McCray -- sold cocaine to former Florida basketball star Vernon Maxwell, 
now with the San Antonio Spurs. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. District Judge Maurice Paul ordered the defendants held without bond until 
sentencing scheduled for Jan. 22. 
</P>
