</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amdahl Corp. Lays Off 400: The Sunnyvale maker of mainframe computer systems 
blamed steep price discounting by International Business Machines, its primary 
competitor, and the strong U.S. dollar for the cuts, which were effective 
Friday and will hit about 5% of its work force. About 80% of the layoffs will 
be made at the company's plants in the Silicon Valley. Amdahl becomes the 
latest of several computer makers to resort to layoffs as conditions in the 
computer industry tighten. 
