<P>
CONFESSION FORCED, RAPE SUSPECT SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-age suspect in the gang rape last spring of a jogger in Central Park 
said that police officers brought him back to the crime scene and tried to 
force him to smear himself with the woman's blood. In a pretrial hearing on the 
admissibility of confessions at the state Supreme Court in Manhattan, Kharey 
Wise, 17, also testified that a detective, in order to force him to confess, 
slapped him so hard he temporarily lost the hearing in his right ear. Wise said 
that police officers brought him to the crime scene two days after the April 19 
attack. Wise and five other youths were indicted for rape and attempted murder. 
In a videotaped confession, Wise admitted holding the jogger while others raped 
her. 
